Text:
The Fortune Dash and the Laughing Rice Cake
events are over!

Finally we are getting to the last contest! "Hagoita
Deathmatch"! Only one participant will be crowned
overall winner and get their hands on the kagami
rice cake!

I wonder how they decide who the winner is. Also,
who came in second or third place in the first
contest?
They decide in order of who was closest!

Hmm... Therianthropes can be so vague. Although, some
participants look quite high-strung...

There'll be no problems if one of us wins the final
Hagoita Deathmatch!
Optimistic of you... Though you are right about that.

But more exactly, what is a Hagoita Deathmatch?
It sounds like a very dangerous event.

The rules are simple! It is a 1-on-1 titanic battle
using a racket and a calligraphy brush!

If you hit the shuttlecock with your racket but it
lands on your side, then you lose! But hitting
the shuttlecock with your calligraphy brush is
against the rules!

He said it was simple, but it's more complex than the
other contests. Are these really the correct rules...?

According to Cid, if you lose then you're supposed to
have your face painted in black ink...

Furthermore, you can interfere with your opponent by
using your calligraphy brush to throw ink. Direct attacks
using your brush or racket are forbidden! Only savages
use brute force to win!

You just hit him really hard and took it. That has to
be against the rules...

And there you have it! In the end, all therianthropes
solve problems through force! The win goes to the
canine therianthrope Delta!
Isn't that the opposite of what he said before?
It's fine as long as it's interesting.

There are other detailed rules too, like you can't
keep the shuttlecock with your racket.

If you do that, it's a foul, and you'll lose a point.
As for the other rules, you'll figure it out! Let's
get started!

Wait, it's a point system? How many points do you
start with?

Round 1, match 1! In the red corner! The Great Ize
Fortune Dash winner, Delta!
Awooo! I'm fired up!
Corner? Ah, I can't keep up with all this.

In the white corner! The winner of last year's Hagoita
Deathmatch! McKen Ro!

This year is my season! I'm gonna roll to the samba
beat!

It's coming! The McKen Samba Style! How will Delta
take on such a formidable foe?!

I can't move well with a brush. I wanna have another
racket instead.

What? The Niita-ryu dual racket style? That
legendary school that disappeared hundreds
of years ago...

Who would have though we'd see a revival of Niita-ryu
in this day and age...
...This event really is in its third year, right?
I'm gonna hit that shuttlecock!
Gyaaah!

Awoo! A strong smash hits McKen directly in the face!
He can't stand up. He loses by violent knockout!
I'm still fired up!

Huh... I should watch carefully and learn as much
of the rules as I can until my turn comes.

Now, the last match of round 1! In the white corner,
the winner of the Laughing Rice Cake! Alphaaaa!

I don't know why, but that title doesn't
ring well...

(But having watched all the matches up to now,
I'm starting to get the rules.)
Haaaaa!

Alpha chooses a straight hit! The shuttlecock flies
high in the sky!
Now!
Urgh, my eyes!

In that moment, she let fly with ink from her brush!
Admirable interference! Alpha gets the first point!

(Just two choices: get points the honest way by
hitting low and quick, or return high and slow
and throw ink for interference.)
Take this!

Oh, Alpha has hit it high again! But her opponent is
on to her!
You won't fool me twice!
You can't use the same hand!
Huh? Uwaaaghh!

Ahhh! She was aiming ink at his feet rather than his
face! He is sliding over the ink! He is down!

(Out of the two options, there's actually another
option. Read your opponent and distract them.
This contest is surprisingly complex.)

Who knew you could compete like this in Hagoita
Deathmatch! Alpha is starting a revolution!

...Or maybe I'm just the first to seriously devise
some tactics...

Now, this contest of Hagoita Deathmatch is heating up
into the finals! Deltaaaaa versus Alphaaaaaaa!

This will decide the winner of the Great Ize-athlon!
On whom will the kagami rice cake smile on?!

(At this point, we know that one of us is getting the
kagami rice cake. I don't care if I lose, but...)

Hehehe, just a bit more to victory! I've finished
off everyone by K.O. so far.

But Lady Alpha took forever to win her matches...
I'm stronger than her!
...What was that?
Eeek...!

It sounds like you have a misunderstanding. You need
some disciplining about who the victorious one is. Haaa!

Ahhh! Alpha hit the shuttlecock up high like before,
but she also threw her brush! Isn't a direct attack a
foul?!
(So fast! I can't avoid it!)

Delta guards her face with both rackets! The
calligraphy brush stopped between them―right
at the tip of her nose!
Defending just as I expected.
Ack―

Alpha jumps up high! She has caught up with the
floating shuttlecock!
Take some time to reflect!
Aroo!

The win is Alpha's! With a forbidden double smash shot
into Delta's face!
I...lost...

The rackets are destroyed, and Delta has lost the will
to fight. Alpha is victorious!
